{"type":"message","id":"a0ba11a2","parentId":"c757a26d","timestamp":"2026-06-26T19:07:27.049Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the 4Geeks token. The user wants to connect to their 4Geeks account using this student token, without writing code themselves.\n\nLet me think about what 4Geeks Academy offers. 4Geeks is a coding bootcamp that has a learning platform (probably at https://platform.4geeks.com or similar). They likely have an API that students can use to access their courses, projects, exercises, etc.\n\nThe Composio search didn't find a direct 4Geeks integration (it found Blackbaud which is unrelated). So this won't be a simple plug-and-play via Composio.\n\nLet me think about the approach:\n\n1. 4Geeks Academy has a public API - they use a token-based authentication for their platform. Students can get their personal token from the developer settings.\n2. The token is a SHA hash (looks like `6853e727ba8243e8fd4afef911953857f167a292` - that's a 40-char hex string, typical of a SHA-1 hash).\n\nI should:\n1. Research what 4Geeks API endpoints are available\n2. Propose a plan to create a simple integration layer (either as a skill or as an MCP server) that lets me interact with the 4Geeks platform\n\nLet me search for 4Geeks API documentation.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_details"},{"type":"text","text":"Bien, tengo el token. Composio no tiene integraciĂłn directa con 4Geeks, asĂ­ que toca armarlo manualmente.\n\nDame un segundo para investigar quĂ© endpoints tiene la API pĂşblica de 4Geeks Academy"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4bc5ba4a1e9348e09a8b8c66","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"4geeks academy API documentation student token endpoints"},"partialArgs":"{\"query\": \"4geeks academy API documentation student token endpoints\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"madrid-spain/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,