{"type":"message","id":"27be67d9","parentId":"cec673ca","timestamp":"2026-06-26T19:11:01.494Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The breatheco.de site uses a Prismic CMS API at `https://4geeks.cdn.prismic.io/api` but that's just the CMS content API. \n\nLooking at the build manifest, it seems breatheco.de is the main student platform with routes like:\n- `/cohort/[cohortSlug]/assignments`\n- `/cohort/[cohortSlug]/student/[studentId]`\n- `/login`\n- `/profile/[slug]`\n- `/survey/token/[token]`\n- `/interactive-exercise/[slug]`\n- `/interactive-exercises`\n\nThe API endpoints aren't directly exposed. Let me look at the chunks for API calls more carefully. The `_app-cf508ba21cd61cdf.js` chunk had these API endpoints: `/api/exit-preview`, `/api/preview`, and `https://4geeks.cdn.prismic.io/api`.\n\nBut the platform API for authentication and user data is probably at `https://breatheco.de/api` or similar. Let me check the login chunk to understand the auth mechanism.\n\nActually, let me check what happens when I try the actual API endpoints that the app calls. The login page and user profile management likely use API routes. Since the app is at breatheco.de, the API is likely at the same domain.\n\nLet me look more carefully.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_details"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0eb34a571e1747cea13aaf08","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Look for API calls in the larger chunks\ncurl -sL --connect-timeout 10 --max-time 20 \"https://breatheco.de/_next/static/chunks/80160-12bf3951f4c9b2c0.js\" 2>&1 | grep -oP '[\"'\"'\"'](https?://[^\"'\"'\"']+?)/(?:api|v1|rest)/[^\"'\"'\"']+|[\"'\"'\"']/(api|v1|rest)/[^\"'\"'\"']+' | sort -u | head -30"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Look for API calls in the larger chunks\\ncurl -sL --connect-timeout 10 --max-time 20 \\\"https://breatheco.de/_next/static/chunks/80160-12bf3951f4c9b2c0.js\\\" 2>&1 | grep -oP '[\\\"'\\\"'\\\"'](https?://[^\\\"'\\\"'\\\"']+?)/(?:api|v1|rest)/[^\\