{"type":"message","id":"cea8749e","parentId":"b291d946","timestamp":"2026-06-26T19:12:44.042Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"That `/api/*` endpoint returns Express-powered JSON responses - this is the API. But it's from the 4geeksacademy.com frontend which uses Prismic.io for content and Next.js for SSR. These seem to be content-management oriented.\n\nThe actual student platform is **breatheco.de** which uses `breathecode.herokuapp.com` as backend but the heroku app seems to be down/not responding properly.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The 4Geeks Academy ecosystem has:\n1. `4geeksacademy.com` - Marketing/content site (Express + Prismic)\n2. `breatheco.de` - Student learning platform (Next.js)\n3. `breathecode.herokuapp.com` - API backend (Heroku, seems down)\n\nSince the Heroku backend returns 404 for all `/v1/*` paths, maybe the API version changed, or maybe it's running on a different URL now.\n\nLet me check what happens when I visit breatheco.de - maybe the API proxy is there.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_details"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_7KHusUS3feWrgOFEWMfO8634","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Maybe the API is proxied through breatheco.de itself\nfor path in \\\n  \"/api/v1/auth/me\" \\\n  \"/api/v1/user/me\" \\\n  \"/api/auth/me\" \\\n  \"/api/me\" \\\n  \"/api/user\"; do\n  echo \"=== breatheco.de$path ===\"\n  code=$(curl -sL --connect-timeout 5 --max-time 8 -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" \"https://breatheco.de$path\" -H \"Authorization: Token 6853e727ba8243e8fd4afef911953857f167a292\" 2>&1)\n  echo \"  $code\"\ndone\n\n# Also check if there's a different base API URL in the Next.js pages\ncurl -sL --connect-timeout 10 --max-time 20 \"https://breatheco.de/_next/static/chunks/175675d1-9e790ce2de607ae6.js\" 2>&1 | grep -oP '[\"'\"'\"'](https?://[^\"'\"'\"' ]+)\"' | grep -v google\\|facebook\\|cdn\\|prismic | sort -u | head -20"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Maybe the API is proxied through breatheco.de itself\\nfor path in \\\\\\n  \\\"/api/v1/auth/me\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"/api/v1/user/me\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"/api/auth/me\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"/api/me\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"/api/user\\\"; do\\n  echo \\\"=== breatheco.de$path ===\\\"\\n  code=$(curl -sL --connect-timeout 5 --max-time 8 -o /dev/null -w \\\"%{http_code}\\\" \\\"https://breatheco.de$path\\\" -H \\\"Authorization: Token 6853e727ba8243e8fd4afef911953857f167a292\\\" 2>&1)\\n  echo \\\"  $code\\\"\\ndone\\n\\n# Also check if there's a different base API URL in the Next.js pages\\ncurl -sL --connect-timeout 10 --max-time 20 \\\"https://breatheco.de/_next/static/chunks/175675d1-9e790ce2de607ae6.js\\\" 2>&1 | grep -oP '[\\\"'\\\"'\\\"'](https?://[^\\\"'\\\"'\\\"' ]+)\\\"' | grep -v google\\\\|facebook\\\\|cdn\\\\|prismic | sort -u | head -20\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"madrid-spain/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782501150802,"responseId":"gen-1782501151-H3Hcl2zrlFn7xsranXKs"}}
