{"type":"message","id":"edf18ed7","parentId":"6ddd3c97","timestamp":"2026-06-26T19:13:54.741Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Perfect! Now I have confirmed:\n1. The API is at `https://breathecode.herokuapp.com`\n2. The token works with `Authorization: Token <token>` header\n3. The user is Pedro (student at 4Geeks Madrid and 4Geeks.com)\n4. The API is the BreatheCode API\n\nNow the user wants me to be able to connect to their 4Geeks account using their student token, without them having to develop code. \n\nThe plan is:\n1. I already have the token in `.env` at `/root/.openclaw/.env`\n2. I need to set up a MCP server or composio tool that I can call\n3. Or I could create a custom tool/skill\n\nSince Composio doesn't have 4Geeks integration, I need to set this up differently.\n\nOptions:\n1. **Create a local MCP server** that wraps the BreatheCode API with their token\n2. **Create a skill** for 4Geeks/BreatheCode API access\n3. **Use composio workbench** to set up proxy_execute or run_composio_tool\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully, the best approach would be to:\n\n1. Read the skill-creator skill to see how to create a proper skill for this\n2. Set up a way for me to call the 4Geeks API consistently\n\nLet me think about the cleanest approach. I can:\n\n1. Create a simple MCP server that uses the breathecode API\n2. Register it as a tool I can call\n\nOr better yet, since I have exec access and composio workbench, I can just call the API directly. But the user wants this to be clean and reusable.\n\nLet me think... The user said \"sin que tenga que desarrollar cĂłdigo de mi parte\" - without having to develop code on their part. So I need to set everything up on my end.\n\nThe simplest approach:\n1. Read the skill-creator skill for structuring this properly\n2. Create a wrapper that lets me call BreatheCode API endpoints\n\nActually, I think creating a proper OpenClaw skill makes the most sense. Let me read the skill-creator skill first.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_details"},{"type":"text","text":"Perfecto, conectado. Eres **Pedro Sanchez**, estudiante en **4Geeks Madrid** y **4Geeks.com**. La API es **BreatheCode** (`https://breathecode.herokuapp.com`).\n\nAhora voy a crear una **skill** para que pueda llamar a la API de 4Geeks de forma reusable, sin que toques cĂłdigo."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_kH2QFr6nonybEbXPh2YV9695","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.3/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.3/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"madrid-spain/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782501223782,"responseId":"gen-1782501224-PwF2gMKCEfvLeshlDmiH"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ae3b8c1b","parentId":"edf18ed7","timestamp":"2026-06-26T19:13:54.761Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_kH2QFr6nonybEbXPh2YV9695","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: skill-creator\ndescription: \"Create, edit, audit, tidy, validate, or restructure AgentSkills and SKILL.md files.\"\n---\n\n# Skill Creator\n\nSkills are compact triggerable workflows. Metadata is always visible; body loads only after trigger; references/scripts/assets load only as needed.\n\n## Hard rules\n\n- Keep `SKILL.md` lean; Codex is already capable.\n- Put only trigger-critical facts in frontmatter `description`.\n- Quote frontmatter `description`.\n- Frontmatter needs `name` + `description`; local OpenClaw skills may also use `metadata`, `homepage`, `allowed-tools`, `user-invocable`, `license`.\n- Prefer noun-phrase descriptions; short generic trigger phrase, not full workflow.\n- Move long examples/docs to `references/`; scripts to `scripts/`; templates/media to `assets/`.\n- No extra README/changelog/setup docs inside a skill unless they are actual task references.\n- Validate YAML frontmatter after edits.\n\n## Shape\n\n```text\nskill-name/\n  SKILL.md\n  scripts/      optional deterministic helpers\n  references/   optional docs loaded only when needed\n  assets/       optional output resources/templates\n  agents/       optional UI metadata\n```\n\n## Good SKILL.md\n\n```markdown\n---\nname: pdf-tools\ndescription: \"Inspect, split, merge, OCR, redact, or convert PDFs with local CLI tools.\"\n---\n\n# PDF tools\n\nUse for PDF manipulation. Prefer deterministic scripts for page edits.\n\n## Workflow\n\n1. Inspect file/page count.\n2. Choose exact operation.\n3. Write output beside input unless user asked otherwise.\n4. Render/verify changed pages.\n```\n\n## Edit workflow\n\n1. Read existing skill and nearby resource names.\n2. Remove generic advice the base model already knows.\n3. Keep brittle command syntax, auth caveats, safety rules, and validation.\n4. Replace tables with bullets unless a table is clearly needed.\n5. Relax prose; fragments ok.\n6. Validate frontmatter and run any script tests touched.\n\n## Validation\n\n```bash\npython skills/skill-creator/scripts/quick_validate.py skills/<name>\npython - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport yaml\nfor p in Path(\"skills\").glob(\"*/SKILL.md\"):\n    text=p.read_text()\n    if not text.startswith(\"---\\n\"):\n        raise SystemExit(f\"missing frontmatter: {p}\")\n    fm=text.split(\"---\",2)[1]\n    yaml.safe_load(fm)\nprint(\"ok\")\nPY\n```\n\n`quick_validate.py` is conservative; repo-local frontmatter may allow keys beyond public skill bundles.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1782501234757}}
{"type":"message","id":"823596b8","parentId":"ae3b8c1b","timestamp":"2026-06-26T19:14:03.378Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the skill structure. Let me create a skill for the 4Geeks BreatheCode API. I'll make it a custom skill that wraps the API endpoints as tools I can use. Since this is about making a skill (a reusable instruction set), I need to:\n\n1. Create the skill directory structure\n2. Write the SKILL.md with the API details\n3. Make a script that acts as a reusable API client\n\nBut actually, thinking more practically - the user wants me to be able to connect to 4Geeks using the token, without them writing code. The best approach here is to:\n\n1. Create a skill that documents the API base URL, auth method, and available endpoints\n2. Create a script that can be called by the skill to interact with the API\n3. This way I can call the skill whenever needed\n\nLet me create this skill.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_details"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_200f28111a4941bd862477a4","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p /root/.openclaw/workspace/skills/4geeks/{scripts,references}"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"mkdir -p /root/.openclaw/workspace/skills/4geeks/{scripts,references}\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"madrid-spain/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782501234763,"responseId":"gen-1782501235-gy5JWhKzFpPxcpItGcBM"}}
