{"type":"message","id":"ef058523","parentId":"06a468e0","timestamp":"2026-06-26T19:16:25.731Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, I've gathered enough information. Let me now build the skill. The key findings are:\n\n**API Base URL:** `https://breathecode.herokuapp.com/v1`\n**Auth:** `Authorization: Token <token>`\n**Token location:** `/root/.openclaw/.env` (key: `4GEEKS_TOKEN`)\n\n**Confirmed working endpoints:**\n- `GET /v1/auth/user/me` - Current user profile (with roles, permissions, etc.)\n- `GET /v1/auth/user/<id>` - User by ID\n- `GET /v1/certificate/me` - My certificates\n\nLet me create a comprehensive skill and a script wrapper.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_details"},{"type":"text","text":"Ya tengo suficiente data. Voy a crear la skill con un script wrapper para hacerlo reusable"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_40b8a9f459b34351babcad10","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/skills/4geeks/scripts/4geeks_api.sh","content":"#!/bin/bash\n# 4Geeks BreatheCode API Wrapper\n# Usage: ./4geeks_api.sh <endpoint> [method] [data]\n#   - endpoint: relative path (e.g., \"auth/user/me\") or full \"method path\"\n#   - method: GET (default), POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE\n#   - data: JSON body for POST/PUT/PATCH\n\nset -e\n\n# Config\nBASE_URL=\"${4GEEKS_API_URL:-https://breathecode.herokuapp.com/v1}\"\nENV_FILE=\"/root/.openclaw/.env\"\n\n# Read token from env file\nif [ -z \"$4GEEKS_TOKEN\" ]; then\n  if [ -f \"$ENV_FILE\" ]; then\n    export \"$(grep '^4GEEKS_TOKEN=' \"$ENV_FILE\" | head -1)\"\n  fi\nfi\n\nif [ -z \"$4GEEKS_TOKEN\" ]; then\n  echo '{\"error\":\"4GEEKS_TOKEN not found. Set it in /.openclaw/.env or export 4GEEKS_TOKEN\"}' >&2\n  exit 1\nfi\n\n# Parse args\nif [ $# -eq 0 ]; then\n  echo \"Usage: $0 <endpoint> [method] [data]\"\n  echo \"  endpoint: relative path like 'auth/user/me'\"\n  echo \"  method: GET (default), POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n\nENDPOINT=\"$1\"\nMETHOD=\"${2:-GET}\"\nDATA=\"${3:-}\"\n\n# Build URL\nURL=\"${BASE_URL}/${ENDPOINT}\"\nURL=\"${URL%/}\"  # Remove trailing slash\n\n# Build curl args\nCURL_ARGS=(-sL --connect-timeout 10 --max-time 30)\nCURL_ARGS+=(-H \"Authorization: Token ${4GEEKS_TOKEN}\")\nCURL_ARGS+=(-H \"Accept: application/json\")\n\nif [ \"$METHOD\" != \"GET\" ]; then\n  CURL_ARGS+=(-X \"$METHOD\")\n  if [ -n \"$DATA\" ]; then\n    CURL_ARGS+=(-H \"Content-Type: application/json\")\n    CURL_ARGS+=(-d \"$DATA\")\n  fi\nfi\n\n# Execute\nHTTP_CODE=$(mktemp)\nRESPONSE=$(curl \"${CURL_ARGS[@]}\" -w \"%{http_code}\" -o \"$HTTP_CODE\" \"$URL\")\nBODY=$(cat \"$HTTP_CODE\")\nrm -f \"$HTTP_CODE\"\n\n# Try to parse as JSON\nif echo \"$BODY\" | python3 -m json.tool > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n  echo \"$BODY\" | python3 -m json.tool\nelse\n  echo \"$BODY\"\nfi\n\n# Exit with error on non-2xx\nif [ \"$RESPONSE\" -lt 200 ] || [ \"$RESPONSE\" -ge 300 ]; then\n  exit 1\nfi"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspace/skills/4geeks/scripts/4geeks_api.sh\", \"content\": \"#!/bin/bash\\n# 4Geeks BreatheCode API Wrapper\\n# Usage: ./4geeks_api.sh <endpoint> [method] [data]\\n#   - endpoint: relative path (e.g., \\\"auth/user/me\\\") or full \\\"method path\\\"\\n#   - method: GET (default), POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE\\n#   - data: JSON body for POST/PUT/PATCH\\n\\nset -e\\n\\n# Config\\nBASE_URL=\\\"${4GEEKS_API_URL:-https://breathecode.herokuapp.com/v1}\\\"\\nENV_FILE=\\\"/root/.openclaw/.env\\\"\\n\\n# Read token from env file\\nif [ -z \\\"$4GEEKS_TOKEN\\\" ]; then\\n  if [ -f \\\"$ENV_FILE\\\" ]; then\\n    export \\\"$(grep '^4GEEKS_TOKEN=' \\\"$ENV_FILE\\\" | head -1)\\\"\\n  fi\\nfi\\n\\nif [ -z \\\"$4GEEKS_TOKEN\\\" ]; then\\n  echo '{\\\"error\\\":\\\"4GEEKS_TOKEN not found. Set it in /.openclaw/.env or export 4GEEKS_TOKEN\\\"}' >&2\\n  exit 1\\nfi\\n\\n# Parse args\\nif [ $# -eq 0 ]; then\\n  echo \\\"Usage: $0 <endpoint> [method] [data]\\\"\\n  echo \\\"  endpoint: relative path like 'auth/user/me'\\\"\\n  echo \\\"  method: GET (default), POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE\\\"\\n  exit 1\\nfi\\n\\nENDPOINT=\\\"$1\\\"\\nMETHOD=\\\"${2:-GET}\\\"\\nDATA=\\\"${3:-}\\\"\\n\\n# Build URL\\nURL=\\\"${BASE_URL}/${ENDPOINT}\\\"\\nURL=\\\"${URL%/}\\\"  # Remove trailing slash\\n\\n# Build curl args\\nCURL_ARGS=(-sL --connect-timeout 10 --max-time 30)\\nCURL_ARGS+=(-H \\\"Authorization: Token ${4GEEKS_TOKEN}\\\")\\nCURL_ARGS+=(-H \\\"Accept: application/json\\\")\\n\\nif [ \\\"$METHOD\\\" != \\\"GET\\\" ]; then\\n  CURL_ARGS+=(-X \\\"$METHOD\\\")\\n  if [ -n \\\"$DATA\\\" ]; then\\n    CURL_ARGS+=(-H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\")\\n    CURL_ARGS+=(-d \\\"$DATA\\\")\\n  fi\\nfi\\n\\n# Execute\\nHTTP_CODE=$(mktemp)\\nRESPONSE=$(curl \\\"${CURL_ARGS[@]}\\\" -w \\\"%{http_code}\\\" -o \\\"$HTTP_CODE\\\" \\\"$URL\\\")\\nBODY=$(cat \\\"$HTTP_CODE\\\")\\nrm -f \\\"$HTTP_CODE\\\"\\n\\n# Try to parse as JSON\\nif echo \\\"$BODY\\\" | python3 -m json.tool > /dev/null 2>&1; then\\n  echo \\\"$BODY\\\" | python3 -m json.tool\\nelse\\n  echo \\\"$BODY\\\"\\nfi\\n\\n# Exit with error on non-2xx\\nif [ \\\"$RESPONSE\\\" -lt 200 ] || [ \\\"$RESPONSE\\\" -ge 300 ]; then\\n  exit 1\\nfi\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"madrid-spain/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782501374571,"responseId":"gen-1782501375-xTDYMGxNpJgDcyGkRdCa"}}
