{"type":"message","id":"62c64252","parentId":"bab9247d","timestamp":"2026-06-26T19:37:43.989Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The chunks use dynamic imports or the page names use different URL encoding. Let me look at the build manifest more carefully to find the correct URL pattern for the cohort assignments page.\n\nActually, the `__BUILD_MANIFEST` showed:\n```\n\"/cohort/[cohortSlug]/assignments\":[e,a,o,s,c,n,m,b,j,u,p,x,T,V,i,\"static/chunks/pages/cohort/[cohortSlug]/assignments-28560384bd195218.js\"]\n```\n\nSo the file is actually stored as `pages/cohort/[cohortSlug]/assignments-28560384bd195218.js` on disk. Let me try with the correct encoding.\n\nWait, it might be that Next.js stores the actual URL path differently. Let me try to directly access the chunk.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_details"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_300b4fa164b9427eb2647621","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try the actual URL with bracket encoding\ncurl -sL --connect-timeout 5 --max-time 10 \\\n  \"https://breatheco.de/_next/static/chunks/pages/cohort/%5BcohortSlug%5D/assignments-28560384bd195218.js\" 2>&1 | \\\n  python3 -c \"\nimport sys, re\ndata = sys.stdin.read()\nfor m in re.finditer(r'[\\\"\\\\']([^\\\"\\\\']{3,80})[\\\"\\\\']', data):\n    path = m.group(1)\n    if any(kw in path.lower() for kw in ['assignment', 'task', 'project', 'deliverable', 'cohort', 'api/', 'v1/', '.get(', 'fetch(']):\n        if path.startswith('/') or 'api' in path or 'get' in path.lower()[:6]:\n            print(path)\n\" 2>&1 | sort -u | head -20"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Try the actual URL with bracket encoding\\ncurl -sL --connect-timeout 5 --max-time 10 \\\\\\n  \\\"https://breatheco.de/_next/static/chunks/pages/cohort/%5BcohortSlug%5D/assignments-28560384bd195218.js\\\" 2>&1 | \\\\\\n  python3 -c \\\"\\nimport sys, re\\ndata = sys.stdin.read()\\nfor m in re.finditer(r'[\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\']([^\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\']{3,80})[\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\']', data):\\n    path = m.group(1)\\n    if any(kw in path.lower() for kw in ['assignment', 'task', 'project', 'deliverable', 'cohort', 'api/', 'v1/', '.get(', 'fetch(']):\\n        if path.startswith('/') or 'api' in path or 'get' in path.lower()[:6]:\\n            print(path)\\n\\\" 2>&1 | sort -u | head -20\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"madrid-spain/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782502654415,"responseId":"gen-1782502655-twlGoLlqjomGAnpQFKbS"}}
