{"type":"message","id":"0c06b72a","parentId":"fe35e6c7","timestamp":"2026-06-26T19:38:29.406Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The JS bundles are mostly React framework/minified code and don't contain the API calls directly. Let me try a different approach - use the breathecode.herokuapp.com API directly with different endpoint patterns, and also look at the actual network calls the platform makes by trying to reverse-engineer from the front-end pages.\n\nLet me try exploring the API with more paths.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_details"},{"type":"text","text":"Vamos directo al grano â€” probando mĂˇs patrones de endpoints contra el API real"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d0aff0ecd05b4d5995f9ba31","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try more endpoint patterns\nfor path in \\\n  \"auth/cohort\" \\\n  \"auth/cohort/me\" \\\n  \"auth/user/me/cohort\" \\\n  \"auth/user/21146/cohort\" \\\n  \"academy/6/cohort\" \\\n  \"academy/cohort\" \\\n  \"cohort?user=21146\" \\\n  \"cohort?academy=6\" \\\n  \"user/21146\" \\\n  \"user/me\" \\\n  \"user/me/cohorts\" \\\n  \"user/me/assignments\" \\\n  \"user/me/projects\"; do\n  code=$(curl -sL --connect-timeout 5 --max-time 8 -w \"%{http_code}\" -o /dev/null \\\n    \"https://breathecode.herokuapp.com/v1/$path\" \\\n    -H \"Authorization: Token 6853e727ba8243e8fd4afef911953857f167a292\" \\\n    -H \"Accept: application/json\" 2>&1)\n  echo \"$code $path\"\ndone"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Try more endpoint patterns\\nfor path in \\\\\\n  \\\"auth/cohort\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"auth/cohort/me\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"auth/user/me/cohort\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"auth/user/21146/cohort\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"academy/6/cohort\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"academy/cohort\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"cohort?user=21146\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"cohort?academy=6\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"user/21146\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"user/me\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"user/me/cohorts\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"user/me/assignments\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"user/me/projects\\\"; do\\n  code=$(curl -sL --connect-timeout 5 --max-time 8 -w \\\"%{http_code}\\\" -o /dev/null \\\\\\n    \\\"https://breathecode.herokuapp.com/v1/$path\\\" \\\\\\n    -H \\\"Authorization: Token 6853e727ba8243e8fd4afef911953857f167a292\\\" \\\\\\n    -H \\\"Accept: application/json\\\" 2>&1)\\n  echo \\\"$code $path\\\"\\ndone\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"madrid-spain/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782502696193,"responseId":"gen-1782502696-gmKS0Qyygfbw4i1RoIaH"}}
{"type":"message","id":"aba3b47c","parentId":"0c06b72a","timestamp":"2026-06-26T19:38:36.822Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_d0aff0ecd05b4d5995f9ba31","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"404 auth/cohort\n404 auth/cohort/me\n404 auth/user/me/cohort\n404 auth/user/21146/cohort\n404 academy/6/cohort\n404 academy/cohort\n404 cohort?user=21146\n404 cohort?academy=6\n404 user/21146\n404 user/me\n404 user/me/cohorts\n404 user/me/assignments\n404 user/me/projects"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":7383,"aggregated":"404 auth/cohort\n404 auth/cohort/me\n404 auth/user/me/cohort\n404 auth/user/21146/cohort\n404 academy/6/cohort\n404 academy/cohort\n404 cohort?user=21146\n404 cohort?academy=6\n404 user/21146\n404 user/me\n404 user/me/cohorts\n404 user/me/assignments\n404 user/me/projects","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782502716812}}
{"type":"message","id":"b788b047","parentId":"aba3b47c","timestamp":"2026-06-26T19:38:53.320Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The API seems pretty limited in what endpoints are actually accessible with a student token. Let me look at the breathecode GitHub repo to find the actual API structure.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_details"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5c79a8a207e74fccbf24fd30","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try with different URL - maybe there's a different version or the API is restructured\n# Check GitHub for the actual breathecode API structure\ncurl -sL --connect-timeout 5 --max-time 10 \"https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=breathecode+api&per_page=5\" 2>&1 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor item in data.get('items', [])[:5]:\n    print(f\\\"{item['full_name']}: {item['description']}\\\")\" 2>&1"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Try with different URL - maybe there's a different version or the API is restructured\\n# Check GitHub for the actual breathecode API structure\\ncurl -sL --connect-timeout 5 --max-time 10 \\\"https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=breathecode+api&per_page=5\\\" 2>&1 | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport sys, json\\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\\nfor item in data.get('items', [])[:5]:\\n    print(f\\\\\\\"{item['full_name']}: {item['description']}\\\\\\\")\\\" 2>&1\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d5af3ee4dae94644b902d2e3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Since cohort endpoints are failing with 404, maybe we need to find them via the actual frontend API calls\n# Let me search the JS chunks for \"cohort\" with more context\ncurl -sL --connect-timeout 10 --max-time 20 \\\n  \"https://breatheco.de/_next/static/chunks/68180-ef0121fcea463ae3.js\" 2>&1 | \\\n  python3 -c \"\nimport sys, re\ndata = sys.stdin.read()\n# Search for function calls with 'cohort' or 'assignment' in them\nfor m in re.finditer(r'.{0,100}(?:cohort|assignment|project|task|deliverable).{0,100}', data, re.I):\n    print(m.group(0)[:200])\n    print('---')\n\" 2>&1 | head -60"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Since cohort endpoints are failing with 404, maybe we need to find them via the actual frontend API calls\\n# Let me search the JS chunks for \\\"cohort\\\" with more context\\ncurl -sL --connect-timeout 10 --max-time 20 \\\\\\n  \\\"https://breatheco.de/_next/static/chunks/68180-ef0121fcea463ae3.js\\\" 2>&1 | \\\\\\n  python3 -c \\\"\\nimport sys, re\\ndata = sys.stdin.read()\\n# Search for function calls with 'cohort' or 'assignment' in them\\nfor m in re.finditer(r'.{0,100}(?:cohort|assignment|project|task|deliverable).{0,100}', data, re.I):\\n    print(m.group(0)[:200])\\n    print('---')\\n\\\" 2>&1 | head -60\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"madrid-spain/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782502716833,"responseId":"gen-1782502717-ylTKrEX188o7ug6grOWF"}}
