{"type":"message","id":"854c5417","parentId":"fc3e401d","timestamp":"2026-06-26T19:39:15.687Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The API returns 404 with HTML for most endpoints. Only `auth/user/me`, `auth/user/<id>`, and `certificate/me` work. The frontend SPA seems to use a different API approach. Let me look at the node-api repository from breatheco-de which I discovered earlier - it's described as \"Collection of re-usable cloud functions for breathecode's API\". And there's also \"python-http-requests-api-tutorial-exercises\" which is for learning.\n\nLet me check the actual breathecode repository for the API structure, or try to look at the GitHub organization directly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_details"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_L6U3pHynadyJkhz6LNxC7148","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check the breatheco-de GitHub org for the actual API repo\ncurl -sL --connect-timeout 5 --max-time 10 \"https://api.github.com/orgs/breatheco-de/repos?per_page=30&sort=updated\" 2>&1 | \\\n  python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor item in data:\n    print(f\\\"{item['name']}: {item.get('description','')[:80]}\\\")\" 2>&1 | head -30"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Check the breatheco-de GitHub org for the actual API repo\\ncurl -sL --connect-timeout 5 --max-time 10 \\\"https://api.github.com/orgs/breatheco-de/repos?per_page=30&sort=updated\\\" 2>&1 | \\\\\\n  python3 -c \\\"\\nimport sys, json\\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\\nfor item in data:\\n    print(f\\\\\\\"{item['name']}: {item.get('description','')[:80]}\\\\\\\")\\\" 2>&1 | head -30\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"madrid-spain/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782502744430,"responseId":"gen-1782502745-Bu8H04PnRv3rs2riWcx