{"type":"compaction","id":"f32768a1","parentId":"a855c4ec","timestamp":"2026-06-26T19:40:00.649Z","summary":"## Goal\nEnable the AI assistant to connect to the user's 4Geeks Academy account using their student API token, without requiring the user to write any code.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- The user must not write any code; the assistant must set up everything\n- The token is stored in `/root/.openclaw/.env` as `4GEEKS_TOKEN=6853e7â€¦a292`\n- The solution must be reusable (a skill that wraps the BreatheCode API)\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Discovered the API base URL: `https://breathecode.herokuapp.com/v1` (token auth via `Authorization: Token <token>` header)\n- [x] Identified the backend as **BreatheCode** (Heroku), previously run by breatheco.de\n- [x] Confirmed working endpoints:\n  - `GET /v1/auth/user/me` â€“ current user profile (returns id, email, roles, permissions, GitHub, etc.)\n  - `GET /v1/auth/user/{id}` â€“ user by ID\n  - `GET /v1/certificate/me` â€“ user certificates\n- [x] Confirmed user identity: **Pedro Sanchez** (id 21146), student at 4Geeks Madrid (id 6) and 4Geeks.com (id 47)\n- [x] Created skill directory: `skills/4geeks/`\n- [x] Wrote initial script `scripts/4geeks_api.sh` as a cURL wrapper\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Fix the `.env` parsing bug in `4geeks_api.sh` (line sourcing `4GEEKS_TOKEN=â€¦` directly fails because the file lacks `export`)\n- [ ] Test the script successfully against the API\n- [ ] Write the `SKILL.md` with endpoint documentation and usage patterns\n\n### Blocked\n- The `.env` file contains `4GEEKS_TOKEN=6853e7â€¦a292` (no `export` prefix, no quotes), so `export \"$(grep...)\"` tries to run the value as a command\n- Need to use `source` or `cut -d=` instead\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Skill-based integration**: Create a local OpenClaw skill (`skills/4geeks/`) instead of a Composio/MCP tool, because Composio has no 4Geeks connector\n- **Script wrapper**: Use a bash script with cURL and JSON formatting to make API calls reusable\n- **Token from `.env`**: Read the token from the existing `/root/.openclaw/.env` file to avoid duplication\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Fix `4geeks_api.sh`: replace `export \"$(grep ...)\"` with proper `.env` parsing (e.g., `source` or `eval` or `cut -d=`)\n2. Test the script: `bash skills/4geeks/scripts/4geeks_api.sh auth/user/me`\n3. Write `SKILL.md` documenting:\n   - API base URL and auth method\n   - Confirmed endpoints with example responses\n   - Instructions for the assistant to call the script\n4. Validate the skill with the `skill-creator` validation script if available\n\n## Critical Context\n- **API Base**: `https://breathecode.herokuapp.com/v1`\n- **Auth Header**: `Authorization: Token {4GEEKS_TOKEN}`\n- **Token Value**: `6853e7â€¦a292` (truncated in logs, actual full hash in `.env`)\n- **User ID**: 21146 (Pedro Sanchez)\n- **Academies**: 4Geeks Madrid (slug `madrid-spain`, id 6) and 4Geeks.com (slug `4geeks-com`, id 47)\n- **Skill path**: `/root/.openclaw/workspace/skills/4geeks/`\n- **Script path**: `/root/.openclaw/workspace/skills/4geeks/scripts/4geeks_api.sh`\n- **Env file**: `/root/.openclaw/.env` (format: `4GEEKS_TOKEN=6853e7â€¦a292`)\n- **Next.js bundle source** at `breatheco.de` confirmed `BREATHECODE_HOST: \"https://breathecode.herokuapp.com\"` as the backend\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nThe user simply said \"ok\", presumably acknowledging previous instructions or work on a 4geeks API script. The broader task appears to be creating or fixing a Bash script that reads a `.env` file to obtain a `4GEEKS_TOKEN` and calls the 4geeks API.\n\n## Early Progress\n- The assistant identified that using `source` on the `.env` file caused errors because of `***` in the value.\n- Edited the script to extract the token using `grep` and `cut` instead of `source`/`export`.\n- Saved the fix and ran the script to test.\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- The script is located at `/root/.openclaw/workspace/skills/4geeks/scripts/4geeks_api.sh`.\n- After the edit, the script now fails with a **bad substitution** error on line 11: `${4GEEKS_API_URL:-https://breathecode.herokuapp.com/v1}`.\n- The suffix likely continues debugging this syntax issue (e.g., escaping colons or using proper variable expansion).\n\n<read-files>\n/.openclaw/.env\n/root/.openclaw/.env\n~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.3/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/skills/4geeks/scripts/4geeks_api.sh\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"e5de6417","tokensBefore":1694,"details":{"readFiles":["/.openclaw/.env","/root/.openclaw/.env","~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.3/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/root/.openclaw/workspace/skills/4geeks/scripts/4geeks_api.sh"]},"fromHook":false}
